---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";

const sections = [
  { id: "tldr", title: "TL;DR" },
  { id: "what-we-collect", title: "What we collect" },
  { id: "what-we-dont", title: "What we don't collect" },
  { id: "where-data-lives", title: "Where data lives" },
  { id: "billing", title: "Billing & subscriptions" },
  { id: "permissions", title: "App permissions" },
  { id: "kids", title: "Kids" },
  { id: "changes", title: "Changes" },
  { id: "contact", title: "Contact" },
];
---

<LegalLayout
  eyebrow="Privacy policy"
  title="What we do with your data."
  lede="Short version: almost nothing. We don't run ads, we don't have a server, and your calculations live on your phone, not ours."
  description="Kârly's privacy policy: no ads, no tracking, no third-party SDKs, no server. Your calculations live on your device."
  lastUpdated="May 13, 2026"
  meta={["v0.2", "Plain English, no lawyer-speak"]}
  sections={sections}
>
  <section id="tldr">
    <h2>TL;DR</h2>
    <div class="callout">
      Kârly is a calculator that runs entirely on your phone. We have no
      server that stores your data. We don&rsquo;t run ads. We don&rsquo;t
      load third-party trackers or analytics SDKs. Your calculations and
      saved history are kept in your phone&rsquo;s local preferences — if you
      uninstall the app, that data is gone.
    </div>
    <p>
      If you want the long version, read on. We&rsquo;ve tried to write it
      like a person, not a legal department.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="what-we-collect">
    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>
      Nothing about you. We don&rsquo;t ask for your name, email, phone
      number, or location. There is no Kârly account to create.
    </p>
    <p>
      The only data the app ever handles is the data you type in yourself —
      item names, costs, sell prices, commission and VAT overrides, shipping
      and operational costs. That data is used for one purpose: to calculate
      the number on your screen.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="what-we-dont">
    <h2>What we don&rsquo;t collect</h2>
    <p>To be specific:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        We do not use AdMob, Meta Audience Network, or any advertising SDK.
      </li>
      <li>
        We do not use Google Analytics, Firebase Analytics, Amplitude,
        Mixpanel, or any analytics SDK.
      </li>
      <li>
        We do not use Crashlytics or any crash reporting SDK that transmits
        data off your device.
      </li>
      <li>
        We do not have a Kârly backend server. There is nothing for us to
        log.
      </li>
      <li>
        We do not request location, contacts, photos, microphone, or camera
        permissions.
      </li>
      <li>
        We do not sell, rent, or share data with third parties because we
        don&rsquo;t have data to sell.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="where-data-lives">
    <h2>Where your data lives</h2>
    <p>
      Saved calculations (your History), your daily usage counter, and your
      language preference are stored locally on your device using the
      platform&rsquo;s standard preferences store (SharedPreferences on
      Android). That storage is encrypted at rest by your phone&rsquo;s
      operating system.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you uninstall the app, this data is removed by the operating system.
      We do not back it up to our servers — because, as mentioned, we
      don&rsquo;t have any.
    </p>
    <p>
      PDF reports you generate are placed in your device&rsquo;s share sheet
      for you to send wherever you like. We don&rsquo;t see them.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="billing">
    <h2>Billing &amp; subscriptions</h2>
    <p>
      If you subscribe to Kârly Pro, the actual billing is handled by your
      platform&rsquo;s app store — Google Play Billing on Android, App Store
      on iOS (when iOS launches). We use RevenueCat to validate subscription
      status on the device.
    </p>
    <p>
      We do not see your card number, billing address, or any payment
      details. The app store handles all of that. We only receive a
      &ldquo;yes/no&rdquo; entitlement: is this device&rsquo;s user a Pro
      subscriber?
    </p>
    <p>
      Google Play&rsquo;s, Apple&rsquo;s, and RevenueCat&rsquo;s own privacy
      policies apply to the data they collect to operate billing:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a class="inline" href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener">
          Google Privacy Policy
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a class="inline" href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" rel="noopener">
          Apple Privacy Policy
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a class="inline" href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy" rel="noopener">
          RevenueCat Privacy Policy
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="permissions">
    <h2>App permissions</h2>
    <p>
      Kârly requests no runtime permissions on first launch. The only
      OS-level capability the app uses is the system share sheet — which is
      what hands a generated PDF off to whichever email or messaging app you
      choose to use.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="kids">
    <h2>Kids</h2>
    <p>
      Kârly is a business tool for adults running a small selling operation.
      We don&rsquo;t market it to children under 13, and we don&rsquo;t
      knowingly collect data from anyone — including children — because we
      don&rsquo;t collect data, full stop.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="changes">
    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      If we ever change anything material — for example, if we add a backend
      (we have no plans to) or introduce any third-party SDK — we will
      update this page, bump the &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date at the top,
      and post a clear notice in the app on the next launch. We won&rsquo;t
      sneak it in.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="contact">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have a question about this policy or want to know exactly what
      data your device is storing, write to
      <a class="inline" href="mailto:hi@nexutility.com">hi@nexutility.com</a>.
      A real person will answer.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top:24px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--subtle)">
      Kârly is a product of NexUtility. Mailing address available on request.
    </p>
  </section>
</LegalLayout>
